1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:07,280
<i>Go and bring me the head of…</i>

2
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,479
…Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet.

3
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,880
<i>I must thank all of you.</i>

4
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:15,400
Had you not come to my aid,
my name would have ended today.

5
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:16,920
<i>It was Phraya Kaipetch.</i>

6
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,400
He killed Duang to silence him.

7
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,160
<i>Cha-li-tang maha cha-li-tang.</i>

8
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:27,520
<i>May you two stay together</i>

9
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:30,160
and grow old together.

10
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:33,120
I wish you a good life partner.

11
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:36,120
Don't fall as low as I did.

12
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:38,560
<i>I'm not losing to you that easily, Wad.</i>

13
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,240
<i>Remember this.</i>

14
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:08,600
<i>My blood flows within you.</i>

15
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:11,400
<i>Never betray me.</i>

16
00:03:11,920 --> 00:03:15,240
<i>Otherwise, you'll learn of something</i>

17
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:18,120
<i>more terrifying than death.</i>

18
00:03:46,080 --> 00:03:47,360
Why did you call me here?

19
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:56,360
I have a bedtime story

20
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,920
to tell you.

21
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,160
<i>After I fell into the ravine,</i>

22
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,120
<i>my master saved me.</i>

23
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:36,280
You're awake already?

24
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,320
Did you save my life?

25
00:04:57,320 --> 00:05:00,640
Fate itself brought you to me.

26
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,560
I will never forget

27
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:26,920
your kindness for as long as I live.

28
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:34,680
In this world, nothing comes

29
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:37,000
without a price.

30
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:44,080
I will repay you by serving you

31
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,640
until my last breath.

32
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,680
Good.

33
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:51,360
Do you want to become
a lord of dark sorcery like me?

34
00:05:56,760 --> 00:06:00,520
<i>I received my master's teachings,</i>

35
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,680
<i>but then…</i>

36
00:06:04,720 --> 00:06:06,120
What are you doing, Master?

37
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,080
Give me your body.

38
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:11,400
<i>Sam pa jit cha mi, mi cha jit pa sam.</i>

39
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:13,640
<i>Sam pa jit cha mi,</i>

40
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:16,200
<i>mi cha jit pa sam.</i>

41
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:19,680
<i>Sam pa jit cha mi,</i>

42
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,600
<i>mi cha jit pa sam.</i>

43
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:28,120
Stop!

44
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,640
You old demon,

45
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:34,400
you were trying to steal my body?

46
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,360
You…

47
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,560
You!

48
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:49,000
<i>I will draw the sacred incantations</i>
<i>up to my throat.</i>

49
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,480
<i>I will draw all spells into my chest.</i>

50
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:55,440
<i>I will raise all sacred incantations</i>
<i>above my crown,</i>

51
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:58,640
<i>and thus the holy master</i>
<i>grants me supremacy over all others.</i>

52
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:02,680
<i>Imani imang imani,</i>

53
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:05,640
<i>ehi klai klai piyan mama.</i>

54
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,440
After that,

55
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,720
I went to the capital.

56
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:32,320
Using the old Diathii's black magic,

57
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:36,400
I advanced step by step
until I became Phraya Kaipetch.

58
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:41,880
Even with power and comfort,

59
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:44,240
there is one thing I never forgot

60
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,280
and never will.

61
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,160
What Wad, your father,

62
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:52,000
and his people did to me.

63
00:07:54,080 --> 00:07:56,160
So I came back for revenge.

64
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,640
You used me.

65
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:07,480
Because you're still useful to me, Lasor.

66
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,080
What are you going to--

67
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,680
I saved you so many times.

68
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:15,280
Now it's time you repay me.

69
00:08:39,280 --> 00:08:40,320
Are you alright?

70
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,559
My heart suddenly started hurting.

71
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,080
You still don't feel better?

72
00:08:46,160 --> 00:08:48,920
Why haven't you
executed Phraya Kaipetch yet?

73
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,200
What are you waiting for?

74
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,200
Kill him!

75
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,440
- What's all that noise?
- Kill him!

76
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:55,800
- Kill him!
- Kill him!

77
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:56,800
- Kill him!
- There.

78
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,920
It's coming from
the front of the residence.

79
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:03,200
We've got a situation.

80
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:07,640
- Kill him!
- Kill him!

81
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:10,840
Calm down. I must take Phraya Kaipetch

82
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,640
to face judgment in court.

83
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,920
Don't listen to him! We should storm in

84
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,720
and execute Phraya Kaipetch ourselves!

85
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:21,160
- Kill him! Get out!
- Calm down!

86
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:24,280
Calm down! This country has laws.

87
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,080
Phraya Kaipetch
must be punished by the law.

88
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:28,760
Everyone, stay calm.

89
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:34,040
This is the governor's residence.
You can't do this here.

90
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,160
Lasor?

91
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:55,640
I've executed Phraya Kaipetch

92
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,240
for all of you.

93
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:04,480
Phraya Kaipetch is really dead.

94
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:06,560
Yes. He's really dead.

95
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,960
From now on,

96
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:11,080
Tha Khiri

97
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,240
will be peaceful forever.

98
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:18,200
- Lasor!
- Lasor!

99
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:23,800
- Lasor!
- Lasor!

100
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:26,200
- Lasor!
- Lasor!

101
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,440
Do you even realize what you've done?

102
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:35,320
Huh?

103
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,760
Didn't you promise

104
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,360
you'd cleanse the spell and ordain?

105
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:44,120
Why did you suddenly
lash out and kill Kaipetch?

106
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:50,360
The villagers were about to storm in.

107
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:53,520
I had to cut it off at the root
and kill him first.

108
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:56,320
You've only made things worse.

109
00:10:57,320 --> 00:11:00,240
You should've done
what I told you and left quietly.

110
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:03,600
Isn't this better?

111
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:07,000
Phraya Kaipetch is dead.
The city is peaceful.

112
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:10,080
And I don't need to become a monk,
hiding behind saffron robes.

113
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:13,480
Everything can go back to the way it was.

114
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,800
So you're saying…

115
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,720
you won't be ordained?

116
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,000
Yes.

117
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,680
I've changed my mind.

118
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:29,120
I'm staying here. I'm not going anywhere.

119
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:33,560
Lasor, what do you mean?

120
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:35,440
I mean

121
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,400
I won't leave you, Dad,

122
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:42,360
or this place.

123
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,280
I'm tired, Dad.

124
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:47,640
And now,

125
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,720
Phraya Kaipetch's men will want revenge.

126
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:54,640
If I cleanse the sorcery,
what will I use to fight them?

127
00:11:57,720 --> 00:12:00,800
If something happens to me,
what about you, Yiwha?

128
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,160
What are you going to--

129
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:58,800
I saved you so many times.
Now it's time you repay me.

130
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,760
<i>Sampajit chami michajit pasam.</i>

131
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:17,320
<i>Sampajit chami michajit pasam.</i>

132
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:30,120
Lasor, your body

133
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,600
is mine now.

134
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:36,120
All that remains is the last fragment
of your spirit waiting to be extinguished.

135
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,400
Just…

136
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:41,440
three more full moons

137
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:49,160
and I will possess your body forever.

138
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,640
Things were finally getting better.

139
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,640
Why did everything turn like this?

140
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,360
The villagers at the market
are praising Lasor

141
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:03,960
for killing Phraya Kaipetch.

142
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:07,000
They even want to raise him up
as the next governor of Tha Khiri.

143
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,040
Not even one night,

144
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:12,000
and Lasor's changed.
It's like he's a different person.

145
00:15:14,800 --> 00:15:16,200
How is that possible, Wad?

146
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,120
I'm wondering the same thing,

147
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:23,840
why he beheaded Petch.

148
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:29,960
His eyes,

149
00:15:30,880 --> 00:15:33,400
his behavior, his words,

150
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,080
it's like he's not the same Lasor.

151
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,400
Something is wrong.

152
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:45,320
Only Lasor can answer that.

153
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,200
Lasor.

154
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:06,360
Have a seat.

155
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:13,840
You came to ask

156
00:16:14,840 --> 00:16:17,120
about my decision
to become the next governor, didn't you?

157
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,000
The people

158
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,280
want a leader like me.

159
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:28,560
Everyone was furious with Kaipetch.
They wanted him dead.

160
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:32,000
Then why didn't you let the law handle it?

161
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:36,600
So we could all go back to living together
peacefully, just as Dad intended?

162
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,200
And how can you be so sure

163
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:47,000
the law could deal with Kaipetch?

164
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:50,040
We had the chance.

165
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,600
Why wouldn't we act ourselves?

166
00:16:56,120 --> 00:16:57,360
But what you did

167
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,280
will only create endless hatred.

168
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:05,599
That's why I must become governor,

169
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:09,200
to have the power to protect you

170
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:10,839
and protect Dad.

171
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,560
But not like this.

172
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,800
Yiwha!

173
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:16,800
The law exists
to keep the poor in their place

174
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:18,400
and protect the interests of the rich.

175
00:17:36,040 --> 00:17:37,040
Yiwha,

176
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:40,000
have you ever seen the poor

177
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:43,120
truly rely on the law?

178
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:47,080
People

179
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,680
just want someone with power
to shield them

180
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:55,400
and meet their needs. That's all.

181
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:00,760
What you want

182
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:03,160
will never happen.

183
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:27,120
I don't want my brother
turning into a vigilante,

184
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,560
using violence to solve problems.

185
00:18:29,640 --> 00:18:30,960
If he does,

186
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,960
we'll be no different from governors

187
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:37,320
like Duang or Phraya Kaipetch.

188
00:18:42,320 --> 00:18:45,400
I think your brother
stayed too close to men like them.

189
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,240
His way of thinking,

190
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:52,960
his way of ruling, it's starting to
resemble Phraya Kaipetch's.

191
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,280
I think

192
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:58,040
my brother is acting strange.

193
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,480
Sometimes,

194
00:19:01,280 --> 00:19:02,840
the way he behaves,

195
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:06,520
it's so much like Phraya Kaipetch
it's frightening.

196
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,520
We'll have to keep an eye on him
from a distance

197
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,640
until Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet

198
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,040
sends a new governor.

199
00:19:16,640 --> 00:19:17,800
By then,

200
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:21,440
if your brother still refuses
to step down as acting governor,

201
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:27,000
it means he's been deceiving us
from the start.

202
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:40,840
Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet appointed Pun

203
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:42,760
to oversee the police unit in Tha Khiri,

204
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,800
replacing Luang Kamchat Phairi
after his exile.

205
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:48,920
Soon, you'll be promoted

206
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,920
to Lady Noree.

207
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,320
I'm still the same old me.

208
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:59,160
Show me some respect, will you?

209
00:19:59,760 --> 00:20:02,440
No matter how high I rise,
I'll always rank below my wife.

210
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:06,880
You've been promoted.

211
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:10,040
Yiam becomes village chief.

212
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:12,600
Bandit Wad has been cleared.

213
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,600
And Lasor…

214
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,000
is about to become governor.

215
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,040
I'm afraid
history is about to repeat itself.

216
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,040
Everything Lasor has done so far
doesn't look good.

217
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:26,280
Maybe he's turned over a new leaf.

218
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:33,160
Making a mistake and fixing it,
that's turning over a new leaf.

219
00:20:34,320 --> 00:20:36,440
Making a mistake and repeating it,
that's just his true nature.

220
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,880
I really hope Lasor can change
like you say.

221
00:22:09,440 --> 00:22:12,640
Yiwha.

222
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,560
Yiwha, can you hear me? Yiwha.

223
00:22:20,040 --> 00:22:21,040
Yiwha.

224
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:26,360
Yiwha.

225
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:31,920
Yiwha.

226
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:41,160
Yiwha.

227
00:22:41,240 --> 00:22:44,440
- Lasor?
- Help me, Yiwha.

228
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:47,320
He's inside my body.
He's going to take it.

229
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:50,560
Who? Who's taking your body?

230
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:53,720
Phraya Kaipetch. He's taken my body.

231
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:55,240
You have to help me, Yiwha.

232
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,800
Lasor!

233
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:00,520
Yiwha.

234
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,480
What's wrong, Yiwha?

235
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,240
Yiwha.

236
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:25,200
No one can help you, Lasor.

237
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:27,680
Your spirit

238
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:30,520
is about to be devoured.

239
00:23:33,280 --> 00:23:36,360
<i>I won't let you use my body for evil!</i>

240
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:39,440
And what can you do? Your body.

241
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:42,760
Your spirit. Your sorcery.

242
00:23:43,440 --> 00:23:47,200
All of it will be mine.

243
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:50,520
I'll use your body to kill Bandit Wad,
your father,

244
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:55,160
and send him to a miserable death,
just like Yod and Niem.

245
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:59,120
<i>No! Don't hurt my father!</i>

246
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:17,800
But it felt so real.

247
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,720
Like Lasor truly wanted my help.

248
00:24:23,960 --> 00:24:25,600
Who could possibly hurt your brother?

249
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:28,760
Phraya Kaipetch is dead.

250
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:31,920
His head is still displayed in front
of the residence. You saw it yourself.

251
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:36,160
And what if he's not really dead?

252
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:59,240
I won't let anyone lay a hand on you.

253
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:08,960
Stop overthinking.

254
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,200
Get ready to go back
to Khuan Phra-ngam with me.

255
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:42,360
Why are you stacking stones, Lasor?

256
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:43,720
Uncle Niem said

257
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:47,320
boat people stack stones like this

258
00:25:47,880 --> 00:25:49,400
as a signal for help.

259
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:52,440
But

260
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:55,120
we're not going out to sea.

261
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,120
Why stack them?

262
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,000
Who knows?

263
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:03,400
One day, I might need your help.

264
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:10,720
Then if I ever see
stones stacked like this,

265
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,800
I'll rush to help you.

266
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:17,840
Lasor.

267
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,160
Lasor.

268
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,320
Lasor.

269
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:52,200
Lasor.

270
00:26:57,080 --> 00:27:00,560
Why are you in my room, Yiwha?

271
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:04,520
Lasor,

272
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:09,080
I'm going back
to Khuan Phra-ngam tomorrow.

273
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:12,360
I don't know when we'll meet again.

274
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:16,240
So I wanted to talk to you.

275
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:17,680
Don't touch me!

276
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:25,560
Yiwha,

277
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:29,960
you're married now.
Stop acting like a child.

278
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:34,600
I'm still your sister.

279
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:37,360
Well,

280
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:42,480
speaking of childhood,
do you remember the stacked stones?

281
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,520
You once said

282
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,760
that if we stacked stones,

283
00:27:47,840 --> 00:27:49,920
it means we were happy.

284
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:53,120
You and Nui even competed

285
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:55,520
to see who was happier.

286
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:05,160
I remember.
And I stacked mine the highest.

287
00:28:11,680 --> 00:28:12,520
Right.

288
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,400
Lasor,

289
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,880
would you like fried fish tonight?

290
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:25,720
I'll cook it myself.

291
00:28:25,800 --> 00:28:28,760
Sure. I remember,

292
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:31,240
your cooking is the best.

293
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:37,160
- Wow.
- Here it is.

294
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:46,800
How is it?

295
00:28:54,040 --> 00:28:56,440
Then I'll go cook it right away.

296
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:08,600
Petch just died,

297
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:14,040
why is his skin rotting so fast?

298
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:17,320
And the blood's already dried,

299
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,640
like a corpse
that's been dead for a long time.

300
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:25,160
It could be the effect of dark sorcery.

301
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:28,160
That might make his body
different from normal people.

302
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:29,920
But Petch was like a cat with nine lives.

303
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:33,000
His skin was invulnerable,
blades couldn't pierce him.

304
00:29:34,400 --> 00:29:37,080
So how was Lasor
able to cut off his head so easily?

305
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:38,640
I have a bad feeling.

306
00:29:40,360 --> 00:29:42,640
This may not be an ordinary death.

307
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:47,200
Dad.

308
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,400
Yiwha, what is it?

309
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:52,280
Lasor…

310
00:29:53,440 --> 00:29:55,400
Lasor? What happened?

311
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:07,520
Who are you?

312
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,000
Dad.

313
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:13,080
I'm Lasor, your son.

314
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:15,880
- Don't you recognize me?
- Don't play games with me.

315
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:17,640
Petch.

316
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:31,680
Sharp as ever, Wad. You recognized me.

317
00:30:31,760 --> 00:30:33,960
Get out of my son's body now.

318
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:40,120
If I don't stay in Lasor's body,

319
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,680
where should I go?

320
00:30:43,360 --> 00:30:44,320
Or…

321
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:48,120
would you prefer
I take over Yiwha instead?

322
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:54,720
Go ahead. Try.

323
00:30:57,120 --> 00:30:58,520
But don't forget.

324
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:01,280
If I die,

325
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:04,880
your son dies with me.

326
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,160
You bastard!

327
00:31:09,320 --> 00:31:10,800
It's time

328
00:31:11,720 --> 00:31:13,560
you paid for what you did to me.

329
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:17,560
<i>Om phrakan deva.</i>
<i>I will annihilate all my enemies.</i>

330
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:20,160
<i>Men and women shall submit to my power.</i>

331
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:23,760
<i>Om, destruction, great destruction.</i>

332
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:26,160
<i>I curse you into madness,</i>

333
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:29,000
<i>writhing to death by my hand!</i>

334
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:31,680
<i>Om phrakan deva. I will--</i>

335
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:39,960
Wad!

336
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,760
You won't escape death for long.

337
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:44,440
Just wait!

338
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:59,760
Wad!

339
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:04,360
Wad!

340
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:07,640
Petch placed dark sorcery on you.
We have to remove it now.

341
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:15,080
Not yet. Not now.

342
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:18,040
You're dying. What are you waiting for?

343
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:21,720
Chaem, there's something
I need you to do for me.

344
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:27,040
Wad.

345
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:54,240
Dad, what's wrong with Lasor?

346
00:32:57,560 --> 00:32:59,280
Lasor has been practicing
dark sorcery for a long time.

347
00:33:00,360 --> 00:33:02,000
That's why his mind isn't right.

348
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:07,200
But that wasn't Lasor, Dad.

349
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:12,960
I'll cleanse the sorcery from him.
He'll become himself again.

350
00:33:14,120 --> 00:33:17,520
You should leave for Khuan Phra-ngam
with Yiam.

351
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,000
Come on.

352
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,560
Don't worry.

353
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:23,520
Go before it gets dark.

354
00:33:42,040 --> 00:33:44,280
Please take care of Lasor for me, Dad.

355
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:47,000
Safe travels, Yiwha.

356
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:49,440
May you begin a new life,

357
00:33:50,960 --> 00:33:52,600
build a new family with Yiam.

358
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:58,440
Don't forget to visit me too, Dad.

359
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,320
Good luck.

360
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:15,120
When you're done, hurry and follow us.

361
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,880
We'll be there soon.

362
00:34:28,679 --> 00:34:29,960
Lasor is with Father Wad.

363
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:33,120
Don't worry, Yiwha.

364
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:39,960
Everyone has their own path.

365
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:42,719
Khuan Phra-ngam isn't far from Tha Khiri.

366
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:45,880
If you miss them,
I'll bring you back often.

367
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:49,960
Let's go.

368
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,680
I'll take care of some matters.
at the police station first.

369
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:39,560
Chang, pack my things for me.

370
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,280
I'll do it.

371
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,600
Thanks, Noree.

372
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:47,480
I'll be back soon.

373
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,040
Okay.

374
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,160
Oh, Dad.

375
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:52,680
Uncle Chaem,

376
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:55,320
where did you go?
You weren't here to see Yiwha off.

377
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:57,600
I had something to handle for Wad.

378
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,400
You all go ahead
and follow Yiam to Khuan Phra-ngam.

379
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:03,280
I'll stay and help Wad here.

380
00:36:04,720 --> 00:36:05,680
Okay.

381
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:09,600
Go pack up.

382
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:12,280
You don't want to reach
Khuan Phra-ngam after dark.

383
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,960
Yes.

384
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:27,160
Wad!

385
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:31,920
Yiwha's gone, right?

386
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:36,040
I told her exactly what you asked me to.

387
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,720
Good.

388
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,080
Now I can finally stop worrying.

389
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:48,600
Wad!

390
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:49,680
Hang in there.

391
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:52,360
I'll hurry and find medicinal herbs
to withdraw the curse.

392
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:53,960
Hang in there.

393
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:10,440
My sorcery centipede

394
00:37:12,040 --> 00:37:14,040
will make you suffer

395
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:16,920
and die slowly.

396
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:19,800
Let's see

397
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:23,160
how many more days you can endure.

398
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:04,320
It's nicer than I expected.

399
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:08,320
Let's go.

400
00:38:39,880 --> 00:38:41,800
I'll fetch water to mop the floor.

401
00:38:41,880 --> 00:38:45,080
You check what's broken and needs fixing.

402
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:52,360
Is this a house or a haunted shack?

403
00:38:58,520 --> 00:39:00,520
That's why I told you all to help.

404
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:09,000
You just want free labor.

405
00:39:10,960 --> 00:39:14,440
If I don't use you,
who am I supposed to use? Dogs?

406
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:16,800
Hey, Yiam.

407
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,400
Watch your mouth.

408
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,400
Enough.

409
00:39:21,480 --> 00:39:23,000
One of you barks,

410
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:25,040
the other understands.

411
00:39:26,120 --> 00:39:27,840
Is this house full of dogs or what?

412
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:29,840
Chang!

413
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:31,880
Noree, stay away from them.

414
00:39:31,960 --> 00:39:33,120
Chang! Hey!

415
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:34,120
Yiam!

416
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:35,960
Pun, help me.

417
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,240
You called me a dog?

418
00:39:37,320 --> 00:39:38,360
Pun, help me.

419
00:39:39,680 --> 00:39:41,760
- Pun, move.
- I'm moving.

420
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:42,680
‪Pun.

421
00:39:56,080 --> 00:39:57,640
Now that everything's settled,

422
00:39:58,240 --> 00:39:59,920
what are you going to do next, Yiam?

423
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:03,880
I'm going to make
Khuan Phra-ngam peaceful again,

424
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:06,040
so people can eat well and sleep well,

425
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:08,680
like when my father was alive.

426
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:13,240
That won't be easy.

427
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:17,040
Right now, the place is full of bandits.

428
00:40:17,840 --> 00:40:19,640
If people have knowledge

429
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:22,680
and a way to earn a living,
they'll have money.

430
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:25,560
And when they have money,
they won't turn to banditry.

431
00:40:25,640 --> 00:40:27,440
They won't sell their wives or children.

432
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:31,120
That's how
Khuan Phra-ngam becomes livable again.

433
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:40,120
You're determined. You never give up.

434
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:44,440
I believe one day you'll succeed,
just like your father.

435
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,760
Dusty. It's so dusty.

436
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:56,760
Move.

437
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:09,360
Khuan Phra-ngam
lies at the foot of the mountains.

438
00:41:09,440 --> 00:41:13,240
The soil here is sandy,
nothing grows well.

439
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:17,560
There are barely any rice fields,
and we rely mostly on rainwater.

440
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:21,360
Even if we fish to sell,
it's not enough to survive.

441
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:24,400
So I'm thinking

442
00:41:25,320 --> 00:41:27,400
of writing to Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet

443
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:29,680
to request new crop varieties.

444
00:41:30,280 --> 00:41:32,240
That way,
we can create jobs for the villagers.

445
00:41:33,320 --> 00:41:34,760
Since I was a child,

446
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:39,200
I've never seen anyone
make a decent living from farming here.

447
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:41,320
Trust me.

448
00:41:51,640 --> 00:41:52,680
I,

449
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:56,360
as acting governor of Tha Khiri,

450
00:41:57,480 --> 00:42:00,280
am willing to continue the trade policies

451
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:02,600
you had with Phraya Kaipetch.

452
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:08,680
You and the black-masked rebels

453
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:10,520
helped overthrow him.

454
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:13,360
Why support us now?

455
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:17,080
In business,

456
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:21,160
there are no true friends
and no permanent enemies.

457
00:42:22,360 --> 00:42:25,880
If interests align, we can talk.

458
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:29,720
You're only the acting governor.

459
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:34,200
If Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet
appoints someone new,

460
00:42:34,280 --> 00:42:38,240
won't our trade collapse?

461
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:41,440
Tha Khiri is crawling
with land and river bandits.

462
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:44,440
No one wants to govern here.

463
00:42:44,520 --> 00:42:45,920
They're afraid of dying.

464
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:49,520
Even if a new governor is sent,

465
00:42:50,240 --> 00:42:51,960
that doesn't mean
he'll make it to Tha Khiri.

466
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,520
Don't you agree?

467
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:05,400
And our profits?

468
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:13,800
I only want

469
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:15,720
one-third.

470
00:43:17,960 --> 00:43:20,680
Everything else remains

471
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:23,600
as stated in your agreement
with Phraya Kaipetch.

472
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:28,640
How can we be sure

473
00:43:29,360 --> 00:43:33,840
that you won't betray us someday?

474
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:39,680
Time will answer

475
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:42,680
whatever doubts you have.

476
00:43:48,760 --> 00:43:50,080
To our partnership.

477
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:55,640
Cheers.

478
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:28,040
I forgot to mention one thing.

479
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:31,320
The liquor you just drank

480
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:33,320
contains a triggered poison.

481
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:36,560
If anyone proves disloyal

482
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:40,640
or dares challenge me,
this is what happens.

483
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:50,160
We…

484
00:44:51,360 --> 00:44:54,960
We will be loyal to you alone.

485
00:45:18,440 --> 00:45:19,840
Hang in there, Wad.

486
00:45:19,920 --> 00:45:21,760
Only Wan Phat Nang Chi

487
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:24,040
can purge the dark sorcery from you.

488
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:51,280
Cold-blooded bastard…

489
00:45:53,320 --> 00:45:55,560
Petch cast a sorcery centipede on you.

490
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:58,200
Anyone else would've died.

491
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:06,320
He wants me to suffer before I die.

492
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:11,480
But I'm tougher than that.
I won't die easily.

493
00:46:12,480 --> 00:46:14,560
If Petch is in Lasor's body,

494
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:17,920
where is the real Lasor?

495
00:46:18,800 --> 00:46:20,040
He's still inside his body.

496
00:46:22,920 --> 00:46:25,200
But Petch has imprisoned his spirit,

497
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:30,200
waiting until he can fully possess him.

498
00:46:32,520 --> 00:46:34,400
And if he succeeds,

499
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:37,640
what happens to Yiwha?

500
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:41,680
Petch and Yiwha's hearts are linked.

501
00:46:42,680 --> 00:46:44,040
If we kill Petch,

502
00:46:45,680 --> 00:46:47,240
Yiwha will die too.

503
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:52,680
I have to find a way to eliminate Petch
before it's too late.

504
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:57,360
How much time do we have left?

505
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:03,280
In three full-moon nights,
there will be a lunar eclipse.

506
00:47:05,120 --> 00:47:08,360
When the shadow swallows the full moon,

507
00:47:09,640 --> 00:47:11,080
Lasor's body

508
00:47:13,240 --> 00:47:15,160
will belong to Kaipetch forever.

509
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:29,640
<i>I, Khun Yod Phithak,</i>
<i>Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam,</i>

510
00:47:30,520 --> 00:47:32,920
<i>write to Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet</i>

511
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:36,600
<i>to propose the promotion of agriculture,</i>

512
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:39,200
<i>so villagers may trial crop varieties</i>

513
00:47:39,280 --> 00:47:41,880
<i>suited to this land</i>

514
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:44,960
<i>and earn a stable living.</i>

515
00:47:45,520 --> 00:47:49,240
<i>I respectfully seek</i>

516
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:52,440
<i>Your Excellency's guidance and support,</i>

517
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:54,440
<i>which would be of the greatest grace.</i>

518
00:48:08,680 --> 00:48:12,840
THE WEAVERBIRD PRINCESS

519
00:48:26,320 --> 00:48:27,840
My little sister's storybook.

520
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:31,440
<i>The Weaverbird Princess.</i>

521
00:48:32,240 --> 00:48:33,400
You want to read it?

522
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:36,680
Yiam,

523
00:48:37,760 --> 00:48:40,440
what are the people in the picture doing?

524
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:45,000
Prince Sapphasit

525
00:48:46,240 --> 00:48:48,600
is learning the spell
of spirit transfer from a hermit.

526
00:48:53,520 --> 00:48:55,240
Is that spell real,

527
00:48:55,800 --> 00:48:58,360
or just a comforting fairy tale?

528
00:48:58,440 --> 00:48:59,600
It's real.

529
00:49:00,720 --> 00:49:03,240
The manuals at Khao Phrom record it.

530
00:49:05,600 --> 00:49:07,400
Though I don't know
why I would want to learn it.

531
00:49:08,320 --> 00:49:09,720
I don't want to be anyone else.

532
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:13,800
I only want to be your Blur.

533
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:47,880
Gambling dens, lottery houses,
opium houses, brothels, liquor houses.

534
00:49:49,120 --> 00:49:50,320
With just these,

535
00:49:50,920 --> 00:49:52,640
I'll be rich beyond belief.

536
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:02,880
<i>Money earned by exploiting others</i>

537
00:50:02,960 --> 00:50:04,600
<i>will one day collapse.</i>

538
00:50:09,240 --> 00:50:10,720
Lasor,

539
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:14,320
your father was a bandit.

540
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:16,720
He robbed people too.

541
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:18,720
<i>My father did it to help others.</i>

542
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:21,600
<i>You do it to feed your greed.</i>

543
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:27,120
It's still robbery.

544
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:29,760
What's the difference?

545
00:50:29,840 --> 00:50:33,080
<i>If I must be a tool</i>
<i>for a bandit like you, I'd rather die.</i>

546
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:42,000
Lasor!

547
00:50:45,320 --> 00:50:48,040
Hey!

548
00:50:50,760 --> 00:50:52,400
Lasor, stop.

549
00:50:59,520 --> 00:51:01,880
Go ahead. If you kill yourself,

550
00:51:02,760 --> 00:51:05,000
your sister dies too. Do it.

551
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:08,600
Try it. Kill yourself.

552
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:28,400
Lasor, soon,

553
00:51:30,240 --> 00:51:32,760
your spirit will shatter.

554
00:51:33,840 --> 00:51:36,200
And when the shadow swallows the moon,

555
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:41,360
I'll possess your body forever.

556
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:50,560
What will you do then, Lasor?
What are you going to do?

557
00:51:55,840 --> 00:51:58,520
<i>I'm going back</i>
<i>to Khuan Phra-ngam tomorrow.</i>

558
00:51:58,600 --> 00:52:00,960
<i>I don't know when we'll meet again.</i>

559
00:52:01,840 --> 00:52:05,200
So I wanted to talk to you.

560
00:52:05,280 --> 00:52:06,600
Don't touch me!

561
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:17,120
Yiwha,

562
00:52:18,200 --> 00:52:21,280
you're married now.
Stop acting like a child.

563
00:52:25,680 --> 00:52:27,520
Lasor has been practicing
dark sorcery for a long time.

564
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:30,440
That's why his mind isn't right.

565
00:52:31,800 --> 00:52:36,440
<i>Help me, Yiwha. Help me.</i>

566
00:52:37,120 --> 00:52:38,280
Lasor.

567
00:52:50,080 --> 00:52:51,080
Lasor?

568
00:52:57,120 --> 00:52:59,280
I just wanted to see you.

569
00:52:59,920 --> 00:53:01,120
Yiwha,

570
00:53:01,720 --> 00:53:03,720
Phraya Kaipetch isn't dead.

571
00:53:03,800 --> 00:53:06,200
He transferred his spirit into my body.

572
00:53:07,320 --> 00:53:08,840
You have to help me.

573
00:53:09,760 --> 00:53:11,440
How can I help?

574
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:25,360
Your heart.

575
00:53:26,520 --> 00:53:27,680
Give it to me.

576
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:58,040
- A nightmare?
- Yiam.

577
00:53:59,360 --> 00:54:00,960
I saw Lasor in my dream.

578
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:05,760
He said Phraya Kaipetch isn't dead.

579
00:54:06,560 --> 00:54:09,560
He transferred his spirit
into Lasor's body.

580
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:15,160
You're turning the story I told you

581
00:54:15,800 --> 00:54:17,400
into something real.

582
00:54:18,040 --> 00:54:19,600
But what if it is real?

583
00:54:20,520 --> 00:54:23,280
Do you know any way to help my brother?

584
00:54:28,320 --> 00:54:29,960
In this world,

585
00:54:31,600 --> 00:54:34,280
if something can be done,
it can be undone.

586
00:54:35,800 --> 00:54:37,360
Sorcery is the same.

587
00:54:38,600 --> 00:54:39,880
Don't overthink it.

588
00:54:41,960 --> 00:54:43,800
Father Wad is with Lasor.

589
00:54:44,920 --> 00:54:46,960
He won't let anything
happen to him easily.

590
00:54:50,400 --> 00:54:51,920
Go to sleep.

591
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:28,840
If Petch finds out
you survived the centipedes,

592
00:55:29,880 --> 00:55:31,520
he'll come after you again.

593
00:55:33,400 --> 00:55:35,600
I must find a way to drive Petch's spirit

594
00:55:36,200 --> 00:55:38,800
out of Lasor's body
before the shadow swallows the moon.

595
00:55:40,800 --> 00:55:43,560
I've heard of spirits entering a body,

596
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:47,240
but never of forcing one out.

597
00:55:51,080 --> 00:55:54,080
If it can enter, it can be expelled.

598
00:55:55,440 --> 00:55:56,880
We just need the method.

599
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:01,160
Old Master Khrua Phut has passed.

600
00:56:02,880 --> 00:56:04,040
Otherwise,

601
00:56:05,120 --> 00:56:06,560
he could guide us.

602
00:56:13,280 --> 00:56:14,480
Chaem.

603
00:56:18,880 --> 00:56:20,200
The astral projection spell.

604
00:56:22,800 --> 00:56:24,120
That's dangerous, Wad.

605
00:56:25,280 --> 00:56:26,600
I have to risk it.

606
00:56:27,360 --> 00:56:30,520
Only Old Master Khrua Phut
can save my son.

607
00:56:38,960 --> 00:56:39,880
Tell me.

608
00:56:41,040 --> 00:56:42,600
If there's anything I can do, I'm willing.

609
00:56:42,680 --> 00:56:45,440
Can I ask you for the Klaikot Lek Lai ?

610
00:56:46,040 --> 00:56:49,440
<i>If it weren't important, you wouldn't ask.</i>

611
00:56:49,520 --> 00:56:52,920
<i>Matiyano matiyaa matithi.</i>

612
00:56:54,680 --> 00:56:57,040
Go on, Wad. Kill your own son.

613
00:56:57,120 --> 00:56:58,800
<i>Are you afraid the Lek Lai dagger</i>

614
00:56:58,880 --> 00:57:01,960
will kill your brother
along with Phraya Kaipetch?

615
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:03,560
<i>If Lasor can truly change,</i>

616
00:57:05,040 --> 00:57:06,240
<i>Yiwha won't be harmed.</i>

617
00:57:06,320 --> 00:57:10,840
<i>I'll awaken the corpse-crows</i>
<i>with</i> ahang thukang namaphatha.

618
00:57:12,840 --> 00:57:13,800
I'll fight him.

619
00:57:13,880 --> 00:57:15,120
But you no longer have sorcery.

620
00:58:05,080 --> 00:58:07,080
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
